This paper focuses on efficient management of spatial data for approximate and exact search, which is a common problem in many areas of computer science. The use of spatial indexing and data analysis frameworks suggests that this paper could belong to cs.DB (databases), cs.IR (information retrieval), or cs.DS (data structures and algorithms). The specific focus on Ball-tree and its improvement suggests that this paper could also belong to cs.AI (artificial intelligence) or cs.LG (machine learning), as these fields often use spatial indexing and search algorithms.
